                            <comment id="13893209" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 09:35:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t we have a ticket about this already? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893210" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 09:36:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is only a problem for OSGi users in Karaf/SMX&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14711239" author="metatech" created="Tue, 25 Aug 2015 13:14:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch which shutdowns the CacheManager only when the last cache was removed.  Tested under Servicemix 5.4.1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14711240" author="metatech" created="Tue, 25 Aug 2015 13:17:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;BTW, shouldn&apos;t there be a &quot;synchronized&quot; in the &quot;doStop()&quot; method, which also modifies the &quot;cacheManager&quot; variable ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14713030" author="metatech" created="Wed, 26 Aug 2015 12:30:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New attachment &quot;camel_multiple_cache_v2.diff&quot; : better version with &quot;synchronized&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15212980" author="metatech" created="Sat, 26 Mar 2016 12:16:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI : V2 implementation (26/08/2015) has been used in prod for 6 months in ServiceMix without issues so far.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15233904" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 10 Apr 2016 06:15:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The latest code is similar to your patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15233938" author="metatech" created="Sun, 10 Apr 2016 06:53:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Claus, sorry the for the mistake in the patch.  Here is a new V3 which is correct (V3 was the version running in PROD on our site).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15234136" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 10 Apr 2016 14:21:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks I have applied the v3 so its part of Camel 2.18.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
